review_text: Well, so I got this and it revitalizes a bunch of my plants that had almost gone dormant and literally nothing could do (Bird of Paradise, Peace Lily etc)However,When it came to Pothos, and I have quite a few of them, it was like a 50/50. 50% of them got better, and it KILLED 50% of them. Really not worth using on Pothos ever. AVOID FOR POTHOS.But for many others, its a godsend.

review_text: Earth Juice company has been around a long time! This Hi-Brix molasses is good for feeding the microbes in your soil, which in turn, feed your plants. I mostly use this E.J. Hi-Brix Molasses for making compost teas. The gallon jug will last you a long time. Plus, "a little bit can go a long way", and with this fertilizer, you do not want to overfeed with molasses (overfeeding with molasses can lead to "lock up" with your plants). Works good with my indoor and outdoor plants. Good for soil and hydroponic applications. Try this molasses out instead of buying Golden Barrel blackstrap molasses, you save some cash too.

review_text: Earth Juice products have been around a long time! Their cal-mag is another great product from them. I use it as a foliar spray (1/2 strength), and also hand fed through the soil. It works with my indoor and outdoor grows.  Many other Cal-mags products on the market have "iron" added. E.J. Cal-Mag does not have iron added to their formula (not derived from Kelp), but if you use a kelp or b-vitamin supplement (like SuperThrive), you will get iron from the kelp supplement you add to your fertilizer program. I purchased this E.J. Cal-Mag from Walmart Online (yes, I was also surprised Walmart Online sells "Earth Juice" products). For just under $12, I could not find another price online even close to how low Walmart had E.J. Cal-Mag pri...
